<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1871-09-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1871-09-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="142" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d142">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 4.</note>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Bancroft</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Fish</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 255.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1871-09-01"><hi rend="italic">September</hi> 1, 1871</date>. (Received September
                                20.)</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose a copy of the note which I have
                            received this day from the German Secretary of State, notifying me
                            formally that the Emperor of Germany has accepted the office of
                            arbitrator in the controversy on the northwestern boundary between the
                            United States and Great Britain.<seg type="margin">Formal acceptance by
                                the Emperor of Germany of the office of Arbitrator.</seg></p>
                        <p>I remain, &amp;c.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>GEO. BANCROFT.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>